{"expireTime":9007200805023353000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-ast-26f51843b6abfa4e554c721396f522e2--","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As users, we hate popups. We never click on them. They’re annoying. They get in the way. But as conversion rate optimizers, they just work. They produce results by making themselves very difficult to ignore, and believe it or not, people do convert on these. Good news, though — somewhere, somehow, someone was able to find a middle ground to this. It’s what we call “exit intent modals” or, if you prefer to sound Google smart, “exit intent interstitials.\"","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":458,"offset":458}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":458,"offset":458}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(You’re more than welcome to ","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":460},"end":{"line":4,"column":30,"offset":489}}},{"type":"raw","value":"<a href=\"#code-for-exit-intent-popup\" class=\"smooth-scroll\">","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":30,"offset":489},"end":{"line":4,"column":90,"offset":549}}},{"type":"text","value":"skip my ramble and go straight to the code","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":90,"offset":549},"end":{"line":4,"column":132,"offset":591}}},{"type":"raw","value":"</a>","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":132,"offset":591},"end":{"line":4,"column":136,"offset":595}}},{"type":"text","value":".)","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":136,"offset":595},"end":{"line":4,"column":138,"offset":597}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":460},"end":{"line":4,"column":138,"offset":597}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In comparison to the intrusive popups that appear as soon as you visit a page (or in some cases, after a slight delay), an exit intent popup appears when the user shows an intent to exit the website (hence the name). This allows for the user to have a better experience on the website by not interrupting their visit until the very end when they’re ready to call it quits.","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":599},"end":{"line":6,"column":373,"offset":971}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":599},"end":{"line":6,"column":373,"offset":971}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<figure>\n  <img src=\"/assets/exit-intent-modal-example.jpg\" alt=\"Example of an exit intent modal\" class=\"img-border\">\n  <figcaption>Exit Intent Modal Example (yes I know you hate it, but read on)</figcaption>\n</figure>","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":973},"end":{"line":11,"column":10,"offset":1191}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now, just so we’re on the same page, I’m not referring to those popups you see on any of those shady websites you've been visiting (you know, the ones that are almost impossible to exit from). Rather, let’s focus on the simple modal that shows up before you leave the website — where you’re free to close your window without being prohibited to do so (or being repeatedly asked if you’re ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1193},"end":{"line":13,"column":389,"offset":1581}}},{"type":"raw","value":"<i>","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":389,"offset":1581},"end":{"line":13,"column":392,"offset":1584}}},{"type":"text","value":"really, really","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":392,"offset":1584},"end":{"line":13,"column":406,"offset":1598}}},{"type":"raw","value":"</i>","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":406,"offset":1598},"end":{"line":13,"column":410,"offset":1602}}},{"type":"text","value":" sure). ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":410,"offset":1602},"end":{"line":13,"column":418,"offset":1610}}},{"type":"raw","value":"<b>","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":418,"offset":1610},"end":{"line":13,"column":421,"offset":1613}}},{"type":"text","value":"I've activated it for this blog post, go ahead and move your mouse off of the browser window","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":421,"offset":1613},"end":{"line":13,"column":513,"offset":1705}}},{"type":"raw","value":"</b>","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":513,"offset":1705},"end":{"line":13,"column":517,"offset":1709}}},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":517,"offset":1709},"end":{"line":13,"column":518,"offset":1710}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1193},"end":{"line":13,"column":518,"offset":1710}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s not magic. It’s not big brother. It’s not a crazy complicated algorithm that some tech scientist invented after years of not seeing sunlight. It’s actually a small, simple script that’s added to your website that detects when the user’s mouse hovers outside of the browser window. It’s usually an action someone takes immediately before exiting out of the tab or browser window.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1712},"end":{"line":15,"column":384,"offset":2095}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1712},"end":{"line":15,"column":384,"offset":2095}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(Bonus: Later on in this post, you’ll get step-by-step instructions on how to add it to your website’s existing lightbox/popup scripts, so keep reading.)","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":2097},"end":{"line":17,"column":154,"offset":2250}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":2097},"end":{"line":17,"column":154,"offset":2250}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Even though this technique has been around for a few years, momentum skyrocketed when ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":2252},"end":{"line":19,"column":87,"offset":2338}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://webmasters.googleblog.com/2016/08/helping-users-easily-access-content-on.html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Google announced","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":88,"offset":2339},"end":{"line":19,"column":104,"offset":2355}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":87,"offset":2338},"end":{"line":19,"column":192,"offset":2443}}},{"type":"text","value":" that as of January 10, 2017, websites would be penalized for the relationship between mobile searches and intrusive interstitials. The search engine giant has picked up on the poor UX these popups cause on smaller screens. The penalty only applies if the interstitial appears on a page directly after arriving from a Google-mobile search result. Nothing is stopping Google from moving forward with a full-fledged desktop initiative, so future-proof now.","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":192,"offset":2443},"end":{"line":19,"column":646,"offset":2897}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":2252},"end":{"line":19,"column":646,"offset":2897}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All of these considerations and the careful planning is more than worth it — exit intent popups convert like crazy, and that’s what you’re here for, yes?","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":2899},"end":{"line":21,"column":154,"offset":3052}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":2899},"end":{"line":21,"column":154,"offset":3052}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Okay, enou