{"type":"raw","value":"<h3>Step 1: Choosing a Lightbox Script</h3>","position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1,"offset":7204},"end":{"line":97,"column":44,"offset":7247}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This could work with any script of choice, but over the years I’ve found ","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1,"offset":7249},"end":{"line":99,"column":74,"offset":7322}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://dimsemenov.com/plugins/magnific-popup/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Magnific Popup","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":75,"offset":7323},"end":{"line":99,"column":89,"offset":7337}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":74,"offset":7322},"end":{"line":99,"column":137,"offset":7385}}},{"type":"text","value":" to be one of the most well documented, versatile, and lightweight popup scripts around. But whatever you do, don’t build a lightbox script from scratch, even though the concept is relatively simple, there are many intricacies to take into consideration in order to provide a good user experience.","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":137,"offset":7385},"end":{"line":99,"column":434,"offset":7682}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1,"offset":7249},"end":{"line":99,"column":434,"offset":7682}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<h3>Step 2: Adding the Exit Intent Listener</h3>","position":{"start":{"line":101,"column":1,"offset":7684},"end":{"line":101,"column":49,"offset":7732}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once Magnific Popup is up and running, add the following code to your main.js — assuming all of your custom js code in a file similarly named file:","position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1,"offset":7734},"end":{"line":103,"column":148,"offset":7881}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1,"offset":7734},"end":{"line":103,"column":148,"offset":7881}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>// Exit intent\nfunction addEvent(obj, evt, fn) {\n  if (obj.addEventListener) {\n    obj.addEventListener(evt, fn, false);\n  } else if (obj.attachEvent) {\n    obj.attachEvent(\"on\" + evt, fn);\n  }\n}\n\n// Exit intent trigger\naddEvent(document, 'mouseout', function(evt) {\n  if (evt.toElement === null && evt.relatedTarget === null && !localStorage.getItem('exitintent_show')) {\n    $.magnificPopup.open({\n      items: {\n        src: '#newsletter-form' //ID of inline element\n      },\n      type: 'inline',\n      removalDelay: 500, //Delaying the removal in order to fit in the animation of the popup\n      mainClass: 'mfp-fade mfp-fade-side', //The actual animation\n    });\n    //localStorage.setItem('exitintent_show', 'true'); // Set the flag in localStorage\n  }\n});</code>\n</pre>","position":{"start":{"line":105,"column":1,"offset":7883},"end":{"line":128,"column":7,"offset":8695}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What we’re doing here is wrapping the Magnific Popup function in an event listener that will detect when the mouse is off of the browser window. Once this happens, the lightbox function will fire. We’ve gone ahead and added a localstorage flag (similar to a cookie) that gets set once the script fires; this prevents us from showing the exit intent to the same visitors.","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1,"offset":8697},"end":{"line":130,"column":371,"offset":9067}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1,"offset":8697},"end":{"line":130,"column":371,"offset":9067}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"raw","value":"<h3>Step 3: The HTML</h3>","position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1,"offset":9069},"end":{"line":132,"column":26,"offset":9094}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"c